mer that kills it really. This basically means you will get to use it once per mob. Now what will you use it for? <br><br>1. Stop a CH. <br>Basically, its <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> going to prevent a CH if you kill a mob in under 40 seconds. This is because most mobs will start CHing at 50% (or 20 seconds into the fight). If you interupt their CH, then that buys you another 10 seconds before the mob starts CHing again, which you cannot interrupt. So that gives you a total of about 40 seconds before the mob has CHed. Most people doing exp do not kill mobs over 55 this fast. And in raids, some non-boss mob getting off a CH is not the end of the world (in fact most such mobs die in under 20 seconds, so never get off their CH even if you do not interrupt).<br><br>2. Stop a Gate.<br>Well, this has the advantage that mobs do not gate till the very end. This gives you a larger margin of time. However, gate is a much faster casting spell, so in my experience, divine stun is not really useful for stopping a gating mob in an experience situation. I have had it work in a raid situation.<br><br>However, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> the biggest problem with divine stun is that it is resisted</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> like any other stun. Now with mobs under 55, I am confident because I can get 2 stuns off and a bash before a mob can gate, and 3 stuns and 2 bashes off on a CHing mob to stop them. That almost assures one will not be resisted unless I am very unlucky. <br><br>But mobs 56+ resist stuns more often (because of less level difference if nothing else), and this only exacerbates the problem. You only get the one stun. Resisted or not, you wait 30 seconds. This just makes things so much worse. Not only do you have to wait for the rare case on a raid when a mob is trying to CH or gate, but then you have to not get resisted. Well this is just too unreliable to be really useful. Most of the time when it really counts, I find I am resisted.<br><br>So, what do I use divine stun for? Pulling mostly. Its also nice for drawing agro, in that I can cast it right after casting a regular stun, rather than waiting for spell gems to come back. It also means I have one stun always available, even when I have other things memed. And its useful on occasions to push mobs around.<br><br>Bottom line, Divine Stun is not useful to interrupt mobs in practically any situation you will get into, but I does have some other utility uses, but nothing I would get excited about spending 9 points on. Get this after you get all the really useful aa skills.<br><br>-Iustus <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124361>Duke Iustus</a><BR>Crusader of Marr <BR>Tarew Marr<BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitefyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitefyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/3/02 4:45:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Paladins with Divine Stun</span><hr size=1> I use it for pulling also. I've tried using it to interupt, but the mob just starts casting right after and gets the CH or gate off anyway. It's pretty much useless. <p><BR><BR><A HREF=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77809"><B>Whitefyre Nobleheart</B></A><BR><B><FONT FACE="Old English Text MT, Arial">Paladin of the 60th Light</FONT></B><BR>If I were an Autobot, I'd be:<br><a href="http://android5.com/misc/tests"><img border=0    src="http://android5.com/misc/tests/autobot/ironhide.gif"  alt="Click to see what Autobot you could be!"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallaorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallaorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/3/02 12:18:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Paladins with Divine Stun</span><hr size=1> I exactly used it twice to try and stop a mob from gating so far (a lvl 55+ mob of course) and i got resisted twice ~tt.<br><br>Right now its only usefull for 2 things, manaless pull and gaining agro a bit faster by casting DS right after a normal stun and not having to wait the spell gem to recycle.<br><br>Forget about stoping CH, DS is a 0 sec stun all this will do is reset their CH time at 10 sec, so in the best case senario it buy you 10 extra seconds more realasticly you gonna get 5-7 sec more to kill a mob before CH.<br><br>Basicly this skill is useless dont get it. Get innate wisdom before, seriously its better. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73233"\>Gallaorn<a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxanderax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xanderax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 6:45:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Paladins with Divine Stun</span><hr size=1> Thank you for your time and information. Really apreciate it. Seems like you would need about 4 to 6 paladins working in perfect coordination for you to be able to try and stop mobs from casting. raid chat channel for just paladins would help there to comunicate resists and lands. In on of the few guilds that didnt look at my class I was playing but the player behind the class. There for we are up to about ten high level paladins. Most of the other guilds have maybe three. /Salutes high level paladins for being stuborn and sticking with the class through all the crap they were given every step of the way. <br><br>    Your Brother in Arms Xanderax Valliant on Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udiondlion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dion DLion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/11/02 1:09:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Paladins with Divine Stun</span><hr size=1> 1. are 60th drakes in ToV immune to Divine Stun (even if mad resists)<br>2. are Kael Giants (and giants in general) still immune to divine stun<br><br>thanx for clarification<br>-dion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/11/02 1:29:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Paladins with Divine Stun</span><hr size=1> I don't have Divine Stun so I'll defer to someone with the skill to give an authoritative answer, but my expectation is that drakes and giants would be immune to stun because dragons and giants are flagged to be immune, regardless of level.  The Divine Stun ability is supposed to extend the level cap from 55 to 60, not to let you stun mobs that are normally flagged as immune to stun. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitefyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitefyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Crusader</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 12:23:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Paladins with Divine Stun</span><hr size=1> Yes both dragons and giants are immune. I still sometimes use it on the white dragons and an extra push to hopefully stop it's CH. It costs no mana and casts fast, so why not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallaorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallaorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 6:14:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Paladins with Divine Stun</span><hr size=1> Some drake arent immune to stun in NTOV, specifically the odd lvl 60 blue drake. But by and large drake will be lvl 61+ and those who will be lvl 60 will typicly be immune to stun.<br><br>Giants, all of them, are immune to all form of stuns including divine stun.<br><br>This skill is useless in its current form, i have said it and i will repeat get innate wisdom first. Hell get natural fire resist first this skill is a waste of 9 points. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73233"\>Gallaorn<a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallaorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallaorn</A> at: 4/12/02 6:15:46 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=92.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=8><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=92.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.threadControl?topicID=92.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=92.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=92.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm14">Norrath and Kunark<option value="pala